      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on tomato plants can be a bit of a mystery, but I'm here to help you dig up the cause. It's possible that your plants are experiencing a bit of \"garden goblin\" stress, where the lower leaves are simply being outcompeted by the newer, greener ones. You might need to prune those yellow leaves to prevent them from sucking the life out of the rest of the plant. Just be careful not to cut too much, or you'll end up with a plant that's more stressed than a goblin in a wizard's dungeon. \n\nHowever, if the issue persists, it's worth checking for pests, diseases, or nutrient deficiencies. Maybe your plants are being nibbled on by those pesky hornworms, or perhaps they're suffering from a fungal infection. A little TLC and some targeted care might be just what they need to get back on track. \n\nTo get to the bottom of things, can you tell me more about your soil, watering schedule, and fertilization routine? That might help me narrow down the cause and suggest some specific solutions.",
